  "fun_fact": "India is home to hundreds of edible leafy greens — many, like Gongura and Amaranth, grow wild and are often mistaken for weeds. They're packed with iron, fibre, and antioxidants. Learning what grows around you — and growing some at home — is one of the easiest ways to eat local and eat well!",
